# Frontend Testing Rules (Extension)

These rules extend the core testing philosophy with frontend-specific practices.

---

## 1. UI Behavior Rule
- Tests must validate user-visible behavior
- Do not test internal state or implementation details
- Prefer interaction-based assertions (what the user sees and does)

---

## 2. Mocking Rule
- All services must be mocked in unit tests
- External API calls must never be real

---

## 3. Rendering Focus
- Assertions must reflect UI output, not internal logic
- Validate rendered content and user interactions

---

## 4. Library Consistency
- Use a single testing framework consistently across the frontend